If you want wings prepared quickly with staff that display good customer service skills, DO NOT GO TO THIS ESTABLISHMENT. The wait times are unbelievably long and when you ask the staff about it they either say that they do not know or display a very bad ghetto attitude. Mind you, this is not indicative of all the staff, as I have had pleasant interactions with several of them.  It's a shame because the wings here are amazing. I mean, they are succulent, juicy, tasty, and I don't know what else to say. If I was waiting this restaurant just on the wings alone, it would be five stars. However factoring in the staff's customer service I have to give this restaurant such a low rating.  I understand that sometimes there will be longer wait times than others, however, there is no reason to have to wait over 90min for 12 wings, especially when the restaurant is less than a quarter full and the counter staff are openly playing around on their phones. This is not an isolated incident and actually happens quite often. I had been here several times for GrubHub and for personal dining, each and every time I kick myself for going back.
